title: Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1991-09-13
lineage: DSBD > DAT > CD > EAC (secure) > Cool Edit > CD Wave > shntool > FLAC16
description: Touch Of Gray, Victim Or The Crime, El Paso, Big River, Cumberland Blues, Althea, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Bird Song Victim Or The Crime, Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Throwing Stones, Not Fade Away, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

reviews.review_text:
First Show Had no idea what was going on, but definitely felt 'it'.  Went with 3 of my best friends, in crisp, new tie dyes.  LOL. 

After listening to this show now, I see that while it had it's moments, it's certainly nothing of EPIC proportions.  That said, the Peggy-O is very nice, Cumberland moves, Scarlet>Fire is of note, and Other One gets pretty nasty.  

This SBD is crisp and nice, and warrants an additional star

4 stars for a good 'un in 91 Its been raining all day and I've just been playing along with this show-- its pretty solid, despite some sloppy playing in places. 

Really, it just sounds like they're having a great time, trying stuff out and sometimes get a little too excited.

But that's a good thing.

Big River is good, Masterpiece really is one, and the Scarlet>Fire is exuberant.  Give it a listen some rainy day.
